Test Plan - Login Dashboard [VWO.com]

1. Test Plan ID
TP-VWO-LD-001

2. Test Plan Name
Test Plan - Login Dashboard [VWO.com]

3. Version
1.0

4. Date
2026-03-14

5. Author
Senior QA Lead Engineer

6. Objective
Validate the Login and Dashboard workflows of app.vwo.com to ensure successful authentication, secure session handling, correct module access, and stable dashboard data rendering for enterprise SaaS users.

7. Scope of Testing
- Functional coverage: Login page, post-login dashboard landing, navigation, role-based access, default widgets.
- Non-functional: Performance, security, usability basics.
- Integration: Identity provider/system API calls, backend data retrieval for dashboard cards/widgets.

8. Test Strategy
Risk-based testing with smoke tests, functional tests, API checks, UI validation, cross-browser checks. Manual exploratory plus scripted regression. Automation candidate: login/dashboard route validation.

9. Test Criteria
Entry Criteria:
- PRD and design signed off
- Staging environment deployed with auth backend and DB
- Test accounts available
- Test data loaded
Exit Criteria:
- All critical/high defects fixed and verified
- ≥95% pass for login/dashboard
- No open Severity 1/2 defects
- Final approval

10. Test Deliverables
- Test plan document
- Test case matrix
- Test data sheet
- Execution results
- Defect reports
- Final QA sign-off

11. Test Schedule
Week 1: PRD review and planning
Week 2: Test case creation and environment setup
Week 3: Functional test execution
Week 4: Regression + non-functional tests
Week 5: Final validation and reporting

12. Resource Requirements
QA Analysts (2), Automation Engineer (1), Dev support (1), staging environment, test management tool.

13. Roles and Responsibilities
QA Lead: overall QA governance
QA Engineers: execute tests, log defects
Automation Engineer: script regression
Dev Team: fix defects
Product Owner: approve criteria and sign-off

14. Test Data Requirements
Valid user credentials, invalid credentials, locked users, role-specific data, dashboard dataset, session timeouts.

15. Environment Requirement
Staging app URL, browser matrix (Chrome, Edge, Firefox), test accounts, network profiles, backend logs.

16. Risk and Mitigation
Risk: Auth instability -> mitigation: early sanity tests.
Risk: Dashboard API latency -> mitigation: retry thresholds.
Risk: Missing role data -> mitigation: seed pre-test data.

17. Assumptions
PRD has complete login/dashboard requirements. No hidden auth flows. Staging mirrors production.

18. Test Metrics
Coverage, pass rate, defect density, severity distribution, MTTR, regression cycle.

19. Dependencies
External IDP/SSO, backend data services, stable deployment.

20. Defect Tracking
Use Jira with [LoginDashboard], severity, steps, environment. Weekly triage.

